<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1-4): Open 5ths in LH (G-D, A-E, B-F#) to match the winter pastoral quality.
  RH moves in diatonic 3rds following chord passing tones. G→Am→Bm chromatic-walk bass
  preserved as G-A-B stepwise in LH bass line.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): Same phrase repeated with fuller voicings (3-note LH chords).
  IV chord (C) gets full C3-E3-G3-C4 position. Texture builds mid-piece.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): Climbing melody to d5 requires RH up to D5. LH follows
  with G2-D3-G3-B3 for I (full 4-note). D7 used diatonically as ⑤7 with C added.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 13-16): Final phrase with Em7→D preparation, Am7→Bm→D7→G cadence.
  Full 4-note LH voicings throughout. RH 3-note triad at final measure.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bass line trace: G→A→B→C→D→G (entire phrase arc from m.1-2 beat by beat).
- Inner voice (RH lower note): D→E→F#→E→D → smooth descent back to D over phrase.
- Measure 16: Bm→D7→G with ③m→⑤7→① is a classical Schenkerian 5-6 motion.
- All F# notes carry accid.ges="s" throughout.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-4: 2-3 note hands, open 5ths — wintry, spacious
- mm. 5-8: Fuller 3-note LH, inner voices emerge — warming
- mm. 9-12: LH 4-note chords, D5 climax in melody — broad and full
- mm. 13-16: Peak then convergence to ①, ⑤7→① final cadence — serene resolution
-->
